description: This file contains the implementation of backend APIs and handler functions for WiFi configuration management in a device, including get/set parameter functions, safety checks, and thread management for operations like factory reset and configuration updates.

methods.name: WiFi_GetParamBoolValue
methods.description: Retrieve Boolean parameter value, such as feature flags or status indicators.

methods.name: WiFi_GetParamIntValue
methods.description: Retrieve Integer parameter value, such as thresholds or counters.

methods.name: WiFi_GetParamUlongValue
methods.description: Retrieve ULONG parameter value, such as radio counts or status.

methods.name: WiFi_GetParamStringValue
methods.description: Retrieve String parameter value, such as region code or configuration blobs.

methods.name: WiFi_SetParamBoolValue
methods.description: Set Boolean configuration parameters, triggering hardware or system changes.

methods.name: WiFi_SetParamStringValue
methods.description: Set String configuration parameters and handle complex configurations like web configs or region codes.

methods.name: WiFiRegion_SetParamStringValue
methods.description: Set WiFi region code, with validation and update logic.

methods.name: Radio_GetEntryCount
methods.description: Retrieve the count of WiFi radio entries.

methods.name: Radio_GetEntry
methods.description: Retrieve a specific radio entry handle based on index.

methods.name: Radio_GetParamBoolValue
methods.description: Get a boolean parameter value for a radio instance, such as Enable or AutoChannelEnabled.

methods.name: Radio_GetParamIntValue
methods.description: Get an integer parameter value for radio, such as MCS, TransmitPower.

methods.name: Radio_GetParamUlongValue
methods.description: Get a ULONG parameter value for radio, such as Status, LastChange, SupportedFrequencyBands.

methods.name: Radio_GetParamStringValue
methods.description: Get a string parameter value for radio, such as Alias, Name, OperatingFrequencyBand, SupportedStandards.

methods.name: Radio_SetParamBoolValue
methods.description: Set a boolean parameter for a radio, such as Enable, AutoChannelEnable, X_COMCAST_COM_DFSEnable.

methods.name: Radio_SetParamIntValue
methods.description: Set an integer parameter for a radio, such as MCS, TransmitPower, Channel, or Mode-specific settings.

methods.name: Radio_SetParamUlongValue
methods.description: Set a ULONG parameter for a radio, such as BeaconInterval, RssiThreshold, or channel-specific configs.

ULONG DPP_GetParamStringValue(ANSC_HANDLE hInsContext,char * ParamName,char * pValue,ULONG * pUlSize)
ULONG DPP_STA_GetParamStringValue(ANSC_HANDLE hInsContext,char * ParamName,char * pValue,ULONG * pUlSize)
